{
  "texts": [
    "The size of the training set has a large positive effect, with a 1.91 multiplicative increase in the odds for each 10-fold increase in training samples.",
    "Thus, a publisher with 1000 articles in the training set is 3.82 times more likely to have correct classification in the test set than a publisher with only 10 articles.",
    "Foreign publishers also prove easier to identify.",
    "Table 5 Median predicted publisher-level accuracies averaged over combinations of the MBFC label (rows) and political bias (columns).",
    "The row headers correspond to (R) reliable, (Q) Questionable Source, (C) Conspiracy Pseudoscience, and (S) Satire."
  ]
}